definition:
Tachycardia, also called
tachyarrhythmia, is a heart rate that exceeds the normal resting
rate. In general, a resting heart rate over 100 beats per minute is
accepted as tachycardia in adults. Heart rates above the resting
rate may be normal (such as with exercise) or abnormal (such as with
electrical problems within the heart). [from Wikipedia]
